post_cb({"14266458": {"Id": "14266458", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>\u00a7 14.1/7 (C++11 N3485) explicitly forbids this: </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_14266394_14266458_0\">A non-type template-parameter shall not be declared to have \ufb02oating point, class, or void type. [ Example:  </p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre><code>template&lt;double d&gt; class X; // error  \ntemplate&lt;double* pd&gt; class Y; // OK  \ntemplate&lt;double&amp; rd&gt; class Z; // OK\n</code></pre>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-01-10T20:12:07.293", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2013-01-10T20:12:07.293", "ParentId": "14266394", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "962089"}, "14266472": {"Id": "14266472", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>That's simple: nontype template parameters have to be compiletime constants of integral type or pointer type, i.e. bool, enums, pointers, pointer-to-members, long, int, short, char. Floating point parameters are not allowed in the current standard.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-01-10T20:12:54.157", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-01-10T20:12:54.157", "ParentId": "14266394", "CommentCount": "2", "OwnerUserId": "1838266"}, "14266444": {"Id": "14266444", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>C++ doesn't support floating-point non-type template parameters unfortunately.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-01-10T20:11:37.693", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-01-10T20:11:37.693", "ParentId": "14266394", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "499449"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_14266394_14266458_0": {"length": 8, "quality": 0.8, "section_id": 60}}, "n3337": {"so_14266394_14266458_0": {"length": 8, "quality": 0.8, "section_id": 55}}, "n4659": {"so_14266394_14266458_0": {"length": 7, "quality": 0.7, "section_id": 62}}}, "14266446": {"Id": "14266446", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>You get that error because <em>non-type template parameters</em> cannot be of type <code>float</code>. They may only be <em>integrals</em>, <em>enumerations</em>, <em>member-pointers</em> or <em>addresses</em>.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2013-01-10T20:11:39.977", "Score": "0", "CreationDate": "2013-01-10T20:11:39.977", "ParentId": "14266394", "CommentCount": "0", "OwnerUserId": "927034"}, "14266394": {"ViewCount": "2013", "Body": "<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_14266394_14266394_0\"><strong>Possible Duplicate:</strong><br>\n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2183087/c-why-cant-i-use-float-value-as-a-template-parameter\">C++: Why can\u2019t I use float value as a template parameter?</a> </br></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I have this class:</p>\n<pre><code>template&lt;typename ValueType, ValueType DefaultValue&gt;\nclass SomeClass\n{\n    public:\n        SomeClass() : m_value(DefaultValue){}\n\n        ValueType m_value;\n};\n</code></pre>\n<p>I want to use it like this:</p>\n<pre><code>SomeClass&lt;int, 1&gt; intObj; //ok\nSomeClass&lt;float, 1.f&gt; floatObj; //error: 'float' : illegal type for non-type template parameter 'DefaultValue'\n</code></pre>\n<p>Can you please explain me why I get this error when using <code>float</code>? </p>\n<p>I want to use something similar to represent RGBA colors and to initialize the channels with default value for different color representations(White for example).</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "14266449", "Title": "C++ template with float arguments", "CreationDate": "2013-01-10T20:09:18.000", "LastActivityDate": "2013-01-10T20:12:54.157", "CommentCount": "5", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-23T10:28:59.187", "PostTypeId": "1", "Tags": "<c++><templates>", "Id": "14266394", "AnswerCount": "5", "Score": "3", "OwnerUserId": "336578", "ClosedDate": "2013-01-10T20:16:45.303", "LastEditorUserId": "-1"}, "14266449": {"Id": "14266449", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>The language does not allow the use of floating-point types as non-type template arguments. For an extensive discussion, see <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2183087/c-why-cant-i-use-float-value-as-a-template-parameter\">Why can't I use float value as a template parameter?</a></p>\n", "LastEditorUserId": "-1", "LastActivityDate": "2013-01-10T20:11:45.283", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2013-01-10T20:11:45.283", "ParentId": "14266394", "CommentCount": "0", "LastEditDate": "2017-05-23T12:34:51.250", "OwnerUserId": "367273"}});